; GT4Amiga: launch the resident monitor at boot. It is the only
; Amiga-side program: it serves the framed binary protocol (peek/poke,
; library calls) AND executes deployed programs via its X opcode.
; GT4A: is already available as a device - FS-UAE mounts the shared
; directory with that label automatically, no Assign needed.
; Guarded so a fresh checkout without a deployed binary boots cleanly.
IF EXISTS GT4A:incoming/monitor
  Run >NIL: GT4A:incoming/monitor
ENDIF
